personalInfo.education: University of North Texas (Business Administration and Entrepreneurship, 2015)

tourBios.intlVics: (2) 2015 Abierto de Bucaramanga [Colombia/DevSeries], Abierto CC de Medellin [Colombia/DevSeries]
tourBios.curYrHigh: Became the first Colombian player to win on Tour. Played in front of his hometown fans in Bogota at the Club Colombia Championship. Earned a sponsor's invitation into the tournament and took advantage. Started the second round five back after a first-round 69. Moved up the leaderboard with a 66 Friday. Was two bejhind Trey Mullinax and Andrew Putnam after 36 holes. Jumped out front with a third-round 66 to take a one-stroke lead over Putnam into the final round. Bogeyed two of the first seven holes to drop out of the lead. Fought his way back with three birdies and two bogeys to tie for the lead. Coming down the stretch, went bogey-par-birdie to close out the tournament. Arrived at the 72nd hole tied for the lead with Richy Werenski and Matt Atkins. Reached the par-5 finishing hole in two and successfully two putted from 45 feet for the win. Was congratulated on the green by close friends Julian Etulain and Rodolpho E. Cazaubon. During the ceremony Colombian star Camilo Villegas reached out via text to show support for his fellow countryman.
tourBios.carHigh: 2015: Started his professional career halfway thru the year with two wins and two other top-4s in his first four starts on the Colombian Tour. His victories the Abierto de Buracamanga and the Abierto del CC de Medellin also counted towards the Developmental Series, a series of events that award status on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica… Won his first career title in Bucaramanga on July 12 by a margin of nine strokes at 270 (-18). He was making just his third start as a pro… Made the cut in two of his four starts on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica, collecting a solo fifth place finish at the Volvo Colombian Classic in Bogota in September… Carded 8 consecutive birdies, 10 thru 17, to set a course record of 8-under 63 on the final round of the Copa Diners Club Mitad del Mundo (DevSeries Grand Final) at Arrayanes CC in Quito, Ecuador. His T7 finish at this event secured him exempt status for the first half of the 2016 season on PGA TOUR Latinoamérica.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Played college golf at the University of North Texas (2011-15), where his teammates included Mexico's Carlos Ortiz and Rodolfo Cazaubón.
tourBios.exmtStatus: Exempt – Finished 6-10 at 2015 PGATLA DevSeries Final (exempt to mid-season reshuffle)
